WEBVTT

1
00:00:25.026 --> 00:00:26.111
Ah. fuck.

2
00:00:27.571 --> 00:00:29.656
It's creepy how you always
sit alone in the dark.

3
00:00:29.739 --> 00:00:31.408
[imitating Dracula]
I cannot condemn you

4
00:00:31.491 --> 00:00:35.620
to live in the bowels of
hell for all eternity.

5
00:00:35.704 --> 00:00:39.749
I love you too much.

6
00:00:40.875 --> 00:00:42.836
- What?
- Gary Oldman? Dracula?

7
00:00:42.919 --> 00:00:45.171
- [sighs] No?
- No.

8
00:00:45.255 --> 00:00:46.339
Oh.

9
00:00:46.423 --> 00:00:50.802
Hey. I gotta... I gotta go bail
Sean out of jail. uh. before work.

10
00:00:51.887 --> 00:00:54.389
But I have a meeting with
your counselor later.

11
00:00:54.472 --> 00:00:55.974
What's he gonna
tell me about you?

12
00:00:56.057 --> 00:01:00.478
He might ask. "How's Alice feeling after
you getting beat up at her soccer game?"

13
00:01:00.562 --> 00:01:02.814
Unless. maybe he doesn't
even know about it.

14
00:01:02.898 --> 00:01:05.275
He was holding an ice
pack to your face.

15
00:01:05.358 --> 00:01:08.028
Oh. Malik. I like that guy.

16
00:01:08.528 --> 00:01:10.071
He was. uh... He was tender.

17
00:01:10.989 --> 00:01:13.491
Hey. um. if you wanna
have dinner tonight…

18
00:01:13.575 --> 00:01:15.285
I'm busy. It's Taco Tuesday.

19
00:01:15.368 --> 00:01:19.539
Ah. yes. My favorite vaguely
racist weekly food holiday.

20
00:01:19.623 --> 00:01:21.833
- [chuckles]
- Who you having tacos with?

21
00:01:22.459 --> 00:01:23.835
[horn honks]

22
00:01:23.919 --> 00:01:24.919
["Psycho Killer" playing]

23
00:01:24.961 --> 00:01:27.881
[singing "Psycho Killer"]

24
00:01:27.964 --> 00:01:30.800
[horn honking rhythmically]

25
00:01:31.551 --> 00:01:33.136
Got it.

26
00:01:33.220 --> 00:01:36.056
You know. if you ever do wanna
have dinner. I'm... I'm around.

27
00:01:36.139 --> 00:01:37.766
I'll... I'll be here.

28
00:01:38.558 --> 00:01:39.768
right in my corner.

29
00:01:40.977 --> 00:01:42.020
Bye.

30
00:01:42.687 --> 00:01:43.730
Love you.

31
00:01:44.856 --> 00:01:47.734
- [Liz] Have a great day.
- [Alice] I'm sure it'll be awesome.

32
00:01:49.653 --> 00:01:52.739
- Say it.
- Not everyone here is a fucking idiot.

33
00:01:52.822 --> 00:01:53.823
Attagirl.

34
00:01:57.118 --> 00:01:59.162
- [cell phone rings]
- [sighs]

35
00:01:59.996 --> 00:02:01.498
[sighs]

36
00:02:02.916 --> 00:02:05.001
- Morning. Jimmy.
- Hey. man.

37
00:02:05.085 --> 00:02:07.796
So I did just what you told me. I
didn't pressure her or anything.

38
00:02:07.879 --> 00:02:10.882
I just casually asked her to have
dinner with me. and guess what?

39
00:02:10.966 --> 00:02:12.884
She basically told
me to go fuck myself.

40
00:02:12.968 --> 00:02:15.637
Could we have this conversation
after I have my coffee?

41
00:02:15.720 --> 00:02:17.055
Nope. Look. I know you said

42
00:02:17.138 --> 00:02:20.475
I'm supposed to let her come to
me. but I'm starting to lose hope.

43
00:02:20.559 --> 00:02:21.827
[Paul] Well. it's
understandable.

44
00:02:21.851 --> 00:02:24.051
You've been trying this
approach for almost ten minutes.

45
00:02:24.104 --> 00:02:25.438
Good sarcasm. Paul.

46
00:02:25.522 --> 00:02:28.567
You can't force it. You were
checked out for almost a year.

47
00:02:28.650 --> 00:02:31.570
I just let you know that I would be
there for you when you were ready.

48
00:02:31.653 --> 00:02:34.239
Alice will have dinner
with you when she's ready.

49
00:02:34.322 --> 00:02:35.740
Until then. you just wait.

50
00:02:35.824 --> 00:02:37.993
That's how it is with
people that you love.

51
00:02:38.868 --> 00:02:39.953
You just said you love me.

52
00:02:40.036 --> 00:02:41.371
No. No. I did not.

53
00:02:41.454 --> 00:02:42.831
Well. it sounded like you did.

54
00:02:42.914 --> 00:02:44.600
I'm not ready to say it
back just yet. but...

55
00:02:44.624 --> 00:02:45.458
[siren wailing]

56
00:02:45.542 --> 00:02:47.669
What's with the
sirens? Where are you?

57
00:02:48.920 --> 00:02:51.756
All right. look. Paul. I'm just
gonna be completely honest with you…

58
00:02:53.758 --> 00:02:55.111
You've been very
supportive lately.

59
00:02:55.135 --> 00:02:56.895
so I decided I was gonna
bring you doughnuts.

60
00:02:56.928 --> 00:02:59.180
Then I got down here
to the doughnut shop

61
00:02:59.264 --> 00:03:00.944
and apparently. this
place has been robbed.

62
00:03:00.974 --> 00:03:03.768
There's shattered glass
and blood everywhere.

63
00:03:03.852 --> 00:03:05.312
Could be jelly.
It's probably jelly.

64
00:03:05.395 --> 00:03:08.607
Anyways… [sighs] …looks like today's
not doughnut day for us. Paul.

65
00:03:08.690 --> 00:03:09.941
but I'll see you at work.

66
00:03:10.025 --> 00:03:11.026
Okay. Bye.

67
00:03:11.693 --> 00:03:13.111
Oh. shit.

68
00:03:14.571 --> 00:03:16.114
Now I want a doughnut.

69
00:03:16.197 --> 00:03:18.742
- [door buzzes]
- [door opens]

70
00:03:20.744 --> 00:03:21.953
[Sean] Thanks for coming.

71
00:03:23.788 --> 00:03:24.956
[door buzzes]

72
00:03:31.588 --> 00:03:33.673
- Morning.
- Fuck you.

73
00:03:36.635 --> 00:03:38.637
How come your folks
didn't come bail you out?

74
00:03:39.221 --> 00:03:40.805
- I never called 'em.
- Oh.

75
00:03:41.389 --> 00:03:45.060
Hey. do you know any lawyers? This
dude is definitely coming after me.

76
00:03:45.143 --> 00:03:49.231
[sighs. groans] Yes. I know one.

77
00:03:49.314 --> 00:03:50.815
Is he like an
asshole or something?

78
00:03:50.899 --> 00:03:54.569
- No. No. no. He is the best.
- Great.

79
00:03:54.653 --> 00:03:57.322
I've just been hiding
from him for a year.

80
00:03:58.782 --> 00:04:00.784
[line ringing]

81
00:04:00.867 --> 00:04:03.495
- [cell phone ringing "Baby One More Time"]
- Oh. my God.

82
00:04:05.622 --> 00:04:07.290
Look. Look. look. look.

83
00:04:07.374 --> 00:04:09.709
- What do I do?
- Answer it.

84
00:04:09.793 --> 00:04:11.086
- I'm not ready.
- You are.

85
00:04:12.796 --> 00:04:15.173
- How do I look?
- Great. but it's just a phone call.

86
00:04:15.257 --> 00:04:17.800
- Oh. my God.
- Just answer it.

87
00:04:18.843 --> 00:04:22.305
- Jimmy?
- Mmm.

88
00:04:23.181 --> 00:04:25.350
- Hello?
- Hi. Brian!

89
00:04:25.433 --> 00:04:27.018
That was normal.

90
00:04:27.102 --> 00:04:30.564
["Frightening Fishes" by
Benjamin Gibbard playing]

91
00:04:57.132 --> 00:04:59.676
[Jimmy] Paul cannot
know about this shit.

92
00:04:59.759 --> 00:05:02.053
- God. you look like ass. Jimmy.
- Yeah. I know.

93
00:05:02.137 --> 00:05:03.305
Is Sean okay?

94
00:05:03.388 --> 00:05:06.433
Sean is fine. but my patient's
husband got fucked up.

95
00:05:06.516 --> 00:05:07.809
[Gaby] What?

96
00:05:07.893 --> 00:05:09.144
- Shh.
- [whispers] Oh.

97
00:05:10.437 --> 00:05:12.439
- What happened to you?
- I fell. man.

98
00:05:13.231 --> 00:05:14.733
- How?
- How?

99
00:05:14.816 --> 00:05:18.486
- I got these new shoes here…
- [Gaby] Mm-hmm.

100
00:05:18.570 --> 00:05:19.905
…and I... They got no grip.

101
00:05:19.988 --> 00:05:21.573
I should've got ones with grip.

102
00:05:21.656 --> 00:05:24.951
Mm-hmm. These non-grippy shoes.
they'll... they'll... they'll fuck you up.

103
00:05:26.077 --> 00:05:29.247
- So. you fell onto your eye?
- Yes.

104
00:05:31.833 --> 00:05:33.376
Oh. you got very
close to me. Okay.

105
00:05:33.460 --> 00:05:35.253
Because of your
non-grippy shoes?

106
00:05:35.337 --> 00:05:37.088
Yeah. [smacks lips] Right on it.

107
00:05:37.172 --> 00:05:38.882
- Like. "Whoa."
- Ah.

108
00:05:38.965 --> 00:05:41.468
- I did this like a cartoon. Paul.
- [Gaby] That's crazy.

109
00:05:41.551 --> 00:05:43.470
- [Jimmy groans]
- Ah.

110
00:05:43.553 --> 00:05:45.433
[Gaby] And then he went
right into a side table.

111
00:05:45.972 --> 00:05:48.225
Do you have any side
or little tables. Paul?

112
00:05:48.308 --> 00:05:50.018
- I do.
- [Gaby] That's cool.

113
00:05:50.101 --> 00:05:53.730
Do you have a TV where you can just
watch tennis matches with people?

114
00:05:53.813 --> 00:05:56.858
As in one of the old ones. the deep.
old. square ones that are very heavy?

115
00:05:56.942 --> 00:05:57.859
Like a Zenith?

116
00:05:57.943 --> 00:06:02.197
Look. I don't have people in my
home. It's not that I'm antisocial.

117
00:06:02.280 --> 00:06:05.575
I'd argue that that's the
definition of antisocial.

118
00:06:05.659 --> 00:06:08.954
I know you do this to shame me
'cause I'm a somewhat private person.

119
00:06:09.037 --> 00:06:12.332
but it just
strengthens my resolve.

120
00:06:12.958 --> 00:06:13.959
"Somewhat private"?

121
00:06:14.584 --> 00:06:18.129
I've known you for years. I've never
been inside your apartment. house.

122
00:06:18.213 --> 00:06:20.173
I have no idea. Never
met your daughter.

123
00:06:20.257 --> 00:06:24.511
- Yeah. what is she like?
- [sighs] She lives in Connecticut.

124
00:06:29.683 --> 00:06:32.477
- Wow. It's like she's in the room.
- [scoffs]

125
00:06:32.561 --> 00:06:33.853
Look. I'm pro-boundaries.

126
00:06:33.937 --> 00:06:35.730
I'm always there
for my patients.

127
00:06:35.814 --> 00:06:38.650
just not for my very
needy colleagues.

128
00:06:38.733 --> 00:06:40.652
- Oh. shit.
- No.

129
00:06:40.735 --> 00:06:41.987
- He means you.
- That was you.

130
00:06:42.070 --> 00:06:43.655
- No. Nuh-uh.
- He meant you.

131
00:06:43.738 --> 00:06:44.882
- He did.
- I'm sorry about her.

132
00:06:44.906 --> 00:06:46.783
My family is for me.

133
00:06:47.534 --> 00:06:49.911
My home is my
Fortress of Solitude.

134
00:06:49.995 --> 00:06:52.205
Fortress of Solitude should
be the name of your memoir.

135
00:06:52.289 --> 00:06:55.083
I'm never gonna tell you
the name of my memoir.

136
00:06:55.166 --> 00:06:57.794
- Very spicy today.
- Well. he's mad because I said.

137
00:06:57.878 --> 00:07:00.297
- "memoir." and clearly it's…
- "Mem-wah."

138
00:07:00.380 --> 00:07:01.941
- "…mem-wah."
- That would make a lot of people mad.

139
00:07:01.965 --> 00:07:04.509
Yeah. This is my peepaw.
and this is my "mem-wah."

140
00:07:04.593 --> 00:07:06.011
[chuckles]

141
00:07:06.094 --> 00:07:09.014
My sister and I have been
acting like teenagers again.

142
00:07:09.097 --> 00:07:10.932
Drinking too much.
staying up late.

143
00:07:11.016 --> 00:07:14.644
Oh. my God. Last night we prank
called our old high school principal.

144
00:07:14.728 --> 00:07:17.314
- Turns out he's dead. so not that fun.
- How'd he die?

145
00:07:17.397 --> 00:07:19.524
He was murdered by the
guidance counselor.

146
00:07:19.608 --> 00:07:21.192
Wow. That's a surprise.

147
00:07:21.276 --> 00:07:23.069
Why are you hiding from me?

148
00:07:23.153 --> 00:07:25.572
Can you move your camera? I
can't see your whole face.

149
00:07:26.406 --> 00:07:27.532
Oh. uh. yeah.

150
00:07:29.200 --> 00:07:30.452
How's that? Is that better?

151
00:07:30.535 --> 00:07:33.288
It's like your chair's moving.
but you're not moving your camera.

152
00:07:33.371 --> 00:07:35.790
That's weird. My chair
is staying totally still.

153
00:07:35.874 --> 00:07:40.086
It must be some sort of weird optical
illusion or a f... uh. maybe it's a filter.

154
00:07:40.170 --> 00:07:42.172
- Ah. Grace. our time is up.
- What?

155
00:07:42.255 --> 00:07:44.400
But I did wanna tell you you're
doing really great. okay?

156
00:07:44.424 --> 00:07:46.009
We'll talk again next week. Bye.

157
00:07:48.011 --> 00:07:49.304
[sighs]

158
00:07:49.387 --> 00:07:52.974
So. the place is. like. hopping
like I've never seen it. okay?

159
00:07:53.058 --> 00:07:54.978
So. I'm thinking I'm just
gonna skate on through.

160
00:07:55.018 --> 00:08:00.398
but guess who just stops everything
and asks me how my day is going?

161
00:08:00.482 --> 00:08:01.650
I bet I know. Dan.

162
00:08:02.150 --> 00:08:03.652
- The barista.
- Yeah!

163
00:08:03.735 --> 00:08:04.945
The fucking barista.

164
00:08:05.028 --> 00:08:06.404
- Again.
- Again.

165
00:08:06.488 --> 00:08:08.823
Why don't you just
make my fucking coffee?

166
00:08:08.907 --> 00:08:10.033
Absolutely.

167
00:08:11.076 --> 00:08:13.870
Or you could just
answer his question.

168
00:08:13.954 --> 00:08:18.541
- I mean. I'm just... Thoughts?
- Have a couple. "Fuck" and "that."

169
00:08:18.625 --> 00:08:20.335
Why should I make small
talk with this guy?

170
00:08:20.418 --> 00:08:22.963
Eh. you know. maybe
it gives him joy.

171
00:08:23.046 --> 00:08:25.715
Hearing about my fucking day
would give him joy. really?

172
00:08:26.466 --> 00:08:28.009
It's definitely my
happy place. Dan.

173
00:08:29.135 --> 00:08:30.470
You wanna know what I think?

174
00:08:31.012 --> 00:08:33.890
I think maybe this whole
"I hate everyone" shtick.

175
00:08:33.974 --> 00:08:36.183
it's... it's led to you
living a pretty isolated life.

176
00:08:36.768 --> 00:08:38.520
Aren't you getting
tired of being lonely?

177
00:08:39.104 --> 00:08:42.148
'Cause I'll tell you something.
I'm fucking lonely. Dan.

178
00:08:44.192 --> 00:08:46.528
I really am quite lonely.

179
00:08:47.862 --> 00:08:48.862
Sucks.

180
00:08:50.282 --> 00:08:52.325
Yeah. [sniffs]

181
00:08:52.909 --> 00:08:53.910
It does.

182
00:08:54.703 --> 00:08:56.538
[sighs]

183
00:08:58.290 --> 00:09:01.084
You feel like some coffee.
Dan? I feel like some coffee.

184
00:09:01.877 --> 00:09:04.462
- Hey there. How may I help you?
- Oh. Stan.

185
00:09:05.005 --> 00:09:06.882
His name's Dan.
Your names rhyme.

186
00:09:06.965 --> 00:09:07.966
That's pretty fun. huh?

187
00:09:08.049 --> 00:09:09.467
I will fucking kill you.

188
00:09:10.051 --> 00:09:12.929
[sucks teeth] Uh. just a
couple Americanos. please.

189
00:09:13.013 --> 00:09:14.598
No problem. How's
your day going?

190
00:09:15.348 --> 00:09:17.851
My day. uh. started out slow.
but now it's picking up.

191
00:09:19.144 --> 00:09:20.144
Dan?

192
00:09:20.812 --> 00:09:24.816
Uh. my day was going
okay. but now it's bad.

193
00:09:25.358 --> 00:09:26.359
[Stan] Tell me about it.

194
00:09:26.443 --> 00:09:29.446
We ran out of oat milk. Everyone
here is losing their shit.

195
00:09:29.529 --> 00:09:31.656
- Fuck oat milk.
- Yes.

196
00:09:32.949 --> 00:09:34.075
Thank you.

197
00:09:34.159 --> 00:09:35.535
I'll get those drinks going.

198
00:09:39.664 --> 00:09:42.709
- [clears throat] Hated that.
- I don't believe you.

199
00:09:43.877 --> 00:09:45.503
Oh. shit. [claps] I gotta run.

200
00:09:45.587 --> 00:09:47.172
Session's over. Have fun.

201
00:09:47.255 --> 00:09:49.216
Wait. You said you
were gonna pay.

202
00:09:50.717 --> 00:09:51.760
[groans]

203
00:09:56.765 --> 00:09:58.642
Hello. Sorry I'm late.

204
00:09:58.725 --> 00:10:00.227
I was with a patient.
but I'm here.

205
00:10:00.310 --> 00:10:01.728
Oh. we started without you.

206
00:10:01.811 --> 00:10:04.064
I didn't know if Liz was
filling in permanently or…

207
00:10:04.147 --> 00:10:06.107
- No. no. Just the two times.
- Three times.

208
00:10:06.191 --> 00:10:08.193
Three... Three times? Okay.

209
00:10:08.276 --> 00:10:09.402
I should go. Should I go?

210
00:10:10.070 --> 00:10:13.031
[pants] Uh. no. It's fine.
The more. the merrier.

211
00:10:13.907 --> 00:10:17.118
- Happy to be here.
- It's quite a shiner.

212
00:10:17.827 --> 00:10:20.956
I mean. obviously.
yesterday was a lot.

213
00:10:21.790 --> 00:10:22.791
I agree.

214
00:10:23.583 --> 00:10:25.585
Thank you for cradling
my head. by the way.

215
00:10:25.669 --> 00:10:30.131
Um. I was just telling Liz that
Alice dropped off the debate team.

216
00:10:30.215 --> 00:10:32.193
- She didn't feel like she had the time…
- [grunts]

217
00:10:32.217 --> 00:10:36.304
…'cause of soccer and everything.
and I... Oh… [stammers] …you go.

218
00:10:36.388 --> 00:10:37.264
[Jimmy] Me? Sure.

219
00:10:37.347 --> 00:10:39.099
Um. well. I agree with Liz.

220
00:10:39.182 --> 00:10:42.894
She's. uh... She's currently very
focused on the... the sport of soccer.

221
00:10:42.978 --> 00:10:47.148
Her English teacher. Mr. Alto. tells
me she isn't very social anymore.

222
00:10:47.232 --> 00:10:49.025
Mr. Alto sounds like a narc.

223
00:10:49.109 --> 00:10:50.586
[chuckles] I don't
care for him either.

224
00:10:50.610 --> 00:10:52.404
- He's my husband.
- Oh. [chuckles]

225
00:10:52.487 --> 00:10:54.155
- Oh. my gosh.
- I think he's great.

226
00:10:54.239 --> 00:10:56.199
- Congratulations.
- I just meant she's distracted

227
00:10:56.241 --> 00:10:58.702
- probably cause he's so handsome.
- Yeah. that's it.

228
00:10:58.785 --> 00:11:01.788
Has Alice started
to look at colleges?

229
00:11:02.747 --> 00:11:07.168
No. I asked her if she wanted to go
to a big state school or a small...

230
00:11:07.752 --> 00:11:09.713
- I'm sorry. You go.
- [Jimmy] Yeah.

231
00:11:09.796 --> 00:11:11.649
Her mom and I took her to
the East Coast last year.

232
00:11:11.673 --> 00:11:15.510
and she fell in love with a few
small liberal arts colleges.

233
00:11:15.594 --> 00:11:18.597
Williams. Amherst. Vassar.

234
00:11:19.222 --> 00:11:20.849
Jimmy. you got this.

235
00:11:20.932 --> 00:11:22.851
- I'm gonna leave you to it.
- Okay.

236
00:11:22.934 --> 00:11:24.574
- It's so good that you're here.
- Thanks.

237
00:11:24.603 --> 00:11:26.730
