00:22:05.076 --> 00:22:07.621
You know… [sighs]

474
00:22:08.538 --> 00:22:12.584
I once overheard you and Tia
talking in the driveway about me.

475
00:22:13.168 --> 00:22:16.463
and you said. "Oh.
she's such a mom."

476
00:22:16.546 --> 00:22:19.591
- You are a mom.
- You didn't mean it as a compliment.

477
00:22:25.639 --> 00:22:28.099
- [Paul] You know you fucked up. right?
- [Jimmy] Yes.

478
00:22:28.183 --> 00:22:29.309
Why would you lie to me?

479
00:22:29.976 --> 00:22:31.645
I mean. the truth was so bad.

480
00:22:32.437 --> 00:22:35.148
This is just unacceptable
in my practice.

481
00:22:35.232 --> 00:22:37.943
You know who the most important
person in your life is right now?

482
00:22:38.026 --> 00:22:40.111
- You.
- No. you shithead.

483
00:22:40.612 --> 00:22:42.864
- Your daughter.
- Right. that's what I meant.

484
00:22:42.948 --> 00:22:45.242
- I'm second.
- Okay.

485
00:22:45.325 --> 00:22:49.246
Do not let your professional
life bleed into your personal.

486
00:22:49.329 --> 00:22:54.793
Alice has a hard enough road. and she
will run like hell if you're not careful.

487
00:22:56.545 --> 00:22:58.630
I'm speaking from
experience here.

488
00:22:58.713 --> 00:23:01.925
- I hear you.
- Do not jeopardize her well-being. Got it?

489
00:23:03.093 --> 00:23:06.846
- A nod is not enough. I want a promise.
- Okay.

490
00:23:06.930 --> 00:23:07.931
Jesus. man.

491
00:23:08.557 --> 00:23:10.267
Say the word.

492
00:23:10.350 --> 00:23:12.060
- Promise.
- Promise.

493
00:23:17.357 --> 00:23:18.525
[Paul sighs]

494
00:23:19.025 --> 00:23:20.610
- Is this yours?
- Nope.

495
00:23:21.903 --> 00:23:23.613
- Woof.
- Thanks. Paul.

496
00:23:25.615 --> 00:23:28.618
I really appreciate
you. Oh. Okay.

497
00:23:28.702 --> 00:23:30.763
- [Sean] Come on. come on. Again?
- [video game beeping]

498
00:23:30.787 --> 00:23:31.931
- You doing a dance now?
- Ha.

499
00:23:31.955 --> 00:23:34.541
- You feeling yourself. huh? [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

500
00:23:34.624 --> 00:23:36.751
Hey. yo. Graham. can
you give us a moment?

501
00:23:36.835 --> 00:23:41.756
- [groans] Okay.
- Thank you. [chuckles]

502
00:23:42.340 --> 00:23:43.508
What's up?

503
00:23:43.592 --> 00:23:45.969
We can't have you
staying here. Sean.

504
00:23:46.052 --> 00:23:47.864
- Come on. Are you serious?
- [Tim] We warned you.

505
00:23:47.888 --> 00:23:50.348
We said one more
time. and you're out.

506
00:23:50.432 --> 00:23:53.184
- It's not good for Graham.
- But this wasn't even a bar fight.

507
00:23:53.268 --> 00:23:54.394
You spent the night in jail.

508
00:23:56.605 --> 00:23:58.148
You need money. Son?

509
00:23:58.857 --> 00:24:01.359
- Nah. I don't need anything.
- I can get you some money.

510
00:24:02.402 --> 00:24:03.737
I don't need anything.

511
00:24:06.323 --> 00:24:07.616
[knocking]

512
00:24:08.408 --> 00:24:12.746
- Hola guapa. qué tal?
- Hola. Liz. I'm gonna speak English.

513
00:24:12.829 --> 00:24:15.749
Thank God. 'cause I took French
in high school like a ding-dong.

514
00:24:15.832 --> 00:24:19.711
- Come on in.
- Hey. um. I was thinking tonight.

515
00:24:19.794 --> 00:24:23.381
I might have dinner with
my dad. if that's okay?

516
00:24:24.466 --> 00:24:26.468
Okay. That's... That's great.

517
00:24:26.551 --> 00:24:29.304
- You should definitely do that.
- Hope you didn't go to any trouble.

518
00:24:29.387 --> 00:24:31.973
No. [chuckles] Go be with
your dad. Say hi for me.

519
00:24:32.057 --> 00:24:33.475
Thanks for being so cool.

520
00:24:33.558 --> 00:24:34.976
["Seventeen" playing]

521
00:24:36.603 --> 00:24:37.812
[sighs]

522
00:24:42.400 --> 00:24:43.401
Shit.

523
00:24:44.903 --> 00:24:45.904
[exhales deeply]

524
00:24:52.827 --> 00:24:53.828
[sighs]

525
00:25:08.969 --> 00:25:10.178
[scoffs] Fuck.

526
00:25:13.306 --> 00:25:14.306
[chuckles]

527
00:25:15.350 --> 00:25:16.518
You motherfucker.

528
00:25:40.875 --> 00:25:42.210
- Hey.
- [Jimmy] Hey.

529
00:25:42.294 --> 00:25:43.854
- Where you going?
- Where do you think?

530
00:25:43.879 --> 00:25:45.088
I'm going to the club.

531
00:25:45.171 --> 00:25:48.383
[beatboxes]

532
00:25:48.466 --> 00:25:49.467
Gonna get crunk.

533
00:25:50.510 --> 00:25:52.679
No. I'm gonna play
pickleball. uh. with Brian.

534
00:25:53.388 --> 00:25:54.388
Oh.

535
00:25:55.557 --> 00:25:58.727
- Are those chicken sandwiches?
- Oh. uh. yeah. It's whatever.

536
00:25:58.810 --> 00:26:01.010
Did you get those for us? You
wanna have dinner with me?

537
00:26:01.730 --> 00:26:03.148
'Cause. wait. if you do.

538
00:26:03.231 --> 00:26:05.942
I'm telling you. I will
cancel pickleball like that.

539
00:26:07.152 --> 00:26:11.656
No. uh. I already told you I have
plans. They're for me and Liz.

540
00:26:11.740 --> 00:26:13.325
Right. yeah. Of course they are.

541
00:26:14.910 --> 00:26:18.538
No problemo. [sighs] Got
excited for a second.

542
00:26:18.622 --> 00:26:22.751
Like. uh. "Yeah. chicken
sandwiches with Alice."

543
00:26:23.501 --> 00:26:26.713
- Go. Have fun.
- Thanks. If you're sure.

544
00:26:26.796 --> 00:26:29.132
Oh. my God. So
sure. Yeah. see ya.

545
00:26:30.091 --> 00:26:31.092
Bye.

546
00:26:34.012 --> 00:26:35.889
- [door opens]
- [phone chimes]

547
00:26:36.723 --> 00:26:37.724
[door closes]

548
00:26:46.024 --> 00:26:49.236
Oh. yeah. [chuckles]

549
00:26:49.319 --> 00:26:51.696
Hey. you only invited
two other guys.

550
00:26:51.780 --> 00:26:54.180
- You were that sure I'd show. huh?
- Everything goes my way.

551
00:26:55.200 --> 00:26:57.327
- I hate it when you say that.
- I'm aware.

552
00:26:57.410 --> 00:26:59.305
- [chuckles]
- Okay. let's do this. You're with me.

553
00:26:59.329 --> 00:27:00.538
Come on.

554
00:27:09.005 --> 00:27:10.507
[Paul sighs]

555
00:27:14.219 --> 00:27:15.220
Come on in.

556
00:27:17.681 --> 00:27:20.892
I can't believe he made up a stupid
game just to get away from me.

557
00:27:20.976 --> 00:27:22.370
I mean. what the
hell is pickleball?

558
00:27:22.394 --> 00:27:25.855
It's only the fastest-growing
sport in America. That's all.

559
00:27:25.939 --> 00:27:28.525
Mmm. whatever. I can't
believe he shot me down.

560
00:27:29.442 --> 00:27:32.082
Well. did you tell him that you
were there to have dinner with him?

561
00:27:32.112 --> 00:27:34.992
I mean. I feel like it was pretty
obvious. I was there. and I had dinner.

562
00:27:35.073 --> 00:27:36.074
[Paul grunts]

563
00:27:36.157 --> 00:27:38.553
[basketball commentators] …again.
got three maneuvers for two.

564
00:27:38.577 --> 00:27:39.828
Yeah!

565
00:27:40.412 --> 00:27:41.572
[Alice] Who are those people?

566
00:27:42.289 --> 00:27:43.957
Stop looking around
and watch the game.

567
00:27:44.040 --> 00:27:45.875
- Were you ever married?
- Shh.

568
00:27:46.501 --> 00:27:48.086
["This Life" playing]

569
00:27:50.046 --> 00:27:51.686
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

570
00:27:51.715 --> 00:27:54.593
- What? I just wanna s... Okay. Okay.
- No.

571
00:28:01.766 --> 00:28:02.766
[slurps]

572
00:28:03.977 --> 00:28:05.937
That's you. Nice!

573
00:28:06.521 --> 00:28:08.273
Pickle. bitch. Boom!

574
00:28:08.356 --> 00:28:11.318
[Brian laughs] Nice.

575
00:28:12.319 --> 00:28:15.155
- [Brian yelps]
- Me! Bri! Bri! Cover me.

576
00:28:15.238 --> 00:28:17.198
- That's me again. That's me. Brian!
- Oh!

577
00:28:18.033 --> 00:28:20.744
- [Brian] Oh! Oh! Oh!
- Yes! Yes! Yeah!

578
00:28:21.369 --> 00:28:23.038
- Ow! [chuckles]
- Oh. shit. Are you okay?

579
00:28:23.121 --> 00:28:24.121
No. I'm fine. I'm fine.

580
00:28:28.001 --> 00:28:29.461
So. we ever gonna talk for real?

581
00:28:31.296 --> 00:28:33.256
Not tonight. Let's serve it up.

582
00:28:36.509 --> 00:28:37.509
Okay.

583
00:28:39.262 --> 00:28:41.389
If you can't be real.
what are we even doing?

584
00:28:41.473 --> 00:28:42.474
Fuck.

585
00:28:50.065 --> 00:28:54.027
[scoffs] You ghosted me for
a year. I wanna know why.

586
00:28:54.611 --> 00:28:55.779
I don't know. Brian.

587
00:28:55.862 --> 00:28:57.364
Yes. you do. Just tell me.

588
00:28:57.948 --> 00:29:00.575
[sighs] It doesn't matter.

589
00:29:00.659 --> 00:29:02.202
- Can we just not do this?
- Tell me.

590
00:29:02.285 --> 00:29:03.912
You were drowning!

591
00:29:03.995 --> 00:29:07.832
I was there trying to pull you
out. and then you just cut me off.

592
00:29:07.916 --> 00:29:09.000
I was your best friend.

593
00:29:09.084 --> 00:29:10.835
- I'm a goddamn ray of light.
- Yeah.

594
00:29:10.919 --> 00:29:12.963
- I am human Zoloft.
- Yes. I know!

595
00:29:13.046 --> 00:29:15.632
And you wouldn't let me be
fucking miserable. Brian.

596
00:29:17.342 --> 00:29:18.426
[Jimmy breathes shakily]

597
00:29:18.510 --> 00:29:21.096
I needed to hit rock bottom and
you wouldn't fucking let me.

598
00:29:21.179 --> 00:29:23.223
You couldn't read
the fucking room.

599
00:29:27.102 --> 00:29:29.789
I'm not trying to make you feel bad.
but it's not fun to be around somebody

600
00:29:29.813 --> 00:29:32.941
who says. "Everything goes my
way." when their wife has died.

601
00:29:36.486 --> 00:29:37.487
Okay?

602
00:29:40.949 --> 00:29:41.950
My wife died. Brian.

603
00:29:47.789 --> 00:29:50.000
I never said everything
goes your way.

604
00:29:52.669 --> 00:29:55.297
- Oh. my God. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

605
00:29:55.380 --> 00:29:59.885
I... [chuckles] That's
my thing. [chuckles]

606
00:30:02.637 --> 00:30:03.637
I'm sorry.

607
00:30:04.806 --> 00:30:07.267
- [phone chimes]
- Sorry.

608
00:30:08.810 --> 00:30:10.937
[inhales sharply] I have to go.

609
00:30:11.605 --> 00:30:12.606
It's okay.

610
00:30:14.357 --> 00:30:16.067
- Love you.
- Yeah. love you. too.

611
00:30:19.029 --> 00:30:20.864
- See you in a year.
- Go fuck yourself.

612
00:30:26.786 --> 00:30:29.414
Whoa! What the fuck?

613
00:30:29.497 --> 00:30:31.166
Hey. Alice. It's okay.

614
00:30:31.249 --> 00:30:34.336
This is. uh. Sean. He
needs a place to crash.

615
00:30:34.419 --> 00:30:37.464
- Sean. this is my daughter. Alice.
- Hey. Alice.

616
00:30:38.798 --> 00:30:40.258
["Do You Wanna Talk" playing]
